NAME
  2png - convert image files in the current directory to PNG
SYNOPSIS
  2png
DESCRIPTION
  2png converts every image file of a variety of lossless formats 
  (tga, bmp, gif, ppm, pbm, pcx, psd, ico, xwd, tif)
  in the current working directory to the PNG format instead.
  Conversion is performed using ImageMagick(1)'s convert(1) utility.
  Original files are sent to the system
  trash using the trash(1) utility, if available.
NOTES
  If missing, the trash(1) utility can be installed via the trash-cli
  package on Debian systems.
SEE ALSO
  ImageMagick(1), convert(1), trash(1)
AUTHOR
  Ryan Armstrong <software@zerker.ca>
